				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{\Delta P}}/{\mathrm{P}}({\mathrm{t}}) = - {\mathrm{K\Delta G}}({\mathrm{t}})$$\end{document}where K is the sensitivity factor derived from the resonance characteristics of the cavity and the dielectric properties of the medium (εr of BiVO4 is taken as 68 F m−1)37. The photoinduced change in the conductance of the sample further correlates to the product of the charge carrier generation yield (ϕ) and the sum of electron and hole mobilities (Σμ), which can be obtained by2ϕΣμ=ΔG∕I0βeFA\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
