				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{\phi}} {\mathrm{\Sigma \mu }} = {\mathrm{\Delta G}}/\left( {{\mathrm{I}}_0{\mathrm{\beta eF}}_{\mathrm{A}}} \right)$$\end{document}where I0 is the incident intensity per pulse, e is the elementary charge, β is the ratio between the inner broad and narrow dimensions of the waveguide, and FA is the fraction of incident photons absorbed within the sample. The laser pulse intensities were adjusted by the use of calibrated filters and varied from 1013 to 1015 photons cm−2 pulse−1.

